From: Bryan Blair <bryan.blair@gqr.com>
Sent: Monday, October 6, 2025 12:10 PM
To: maura.pagano@aditumbio.com <maura.pagano@aditumbio.com>
Subject: Submit: Aditum Bio - VP Clinical Development, Immunology - Eric Meltzer, MD

Hi Maura,

Eric Meltzer, MD is currently a Consultant with 20+ years of medical research experience and 12+ years in the pharmaceutical industry. He spent 7 years at Novartis (2013-2020) as Associate Director/Director of Translational Medicine leading early-phase programs and has held three consecutive VP-level positions at Structure Therapeutics, Pieris Pharmaceuticals, and Translate Bio. His immunology credentials include leading programs targeting IL-13, IL-18, IL-1 beta, and A2B receptors across multiple indications (respiratory, rheumatoid arthritis, Sjogren's, musculoskeletal disease), with proven expertise in IND/CTA submissions (2 INDs, 7 CTAs), first-in-human trials, and proof-of-concept study design.

Eric is attracted to Aditum's portfolio model of working across 3-4 biotechs simultaneously, which aligns with his consulting approach of contributing to multiple promising drug development programs. He values both strategy development and hands-on execution, and is explicitly results-driven. He has existing relationships with Mark Fishman (worked under him at Novartis, presented at board meetings) and Dan Meyers (personal friends), which should facilitate rapid integration. He would be seeking a VP Clinical Development title with $430-440K base but remains open in consideration of total package. He lives in Lexington, MA and would work out of your Cambridge location a minimum of 3 days per week onsite.


Eric B. Meltzer, MD

  *
Principal Consultant & Founder, Medicines Development Consulting, Lexington, MA
  *
MD, SUNY Brooklyn; Pulmonary & Critical Care fellowships at Yale & Duke
  *
20+ years medical research; 12+ years pharmaceutical industry
  *
Project/team leader for 7 programs at Novartis; submitted 2 INDs, 7 CTAs; medical monitor for first-in-human trials for 2 novel compounds
  *
Led A2B receptor inhibitor Phase 2 trial across 4 indications (RA, Sjogren's, oncology, IPF) with 7 countries, 40 sites
  *
VP Clinical Development roles at Structure Therapeutics (cardiopulmonary/respiratory franchise), Pieris (respiratory disease area), Translate Bio (all clinical development)
  *
Early-stage development (pre-IND through Phase 2), IND/CTA preparation, regulatory interactions (FDA/EMA), medical monitoring, safety assessment, first-in-human and proof-of-concept trial design, immunology targets across multiple therapeutic areas, cross-functional leadership, KOL management

Best,
Bryan


